[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > One important note on the data: this example generates synthetic utilization data so you can run it without access to a real claims warehouse. The patterns are realistic (modeled after typical commercial health plan distributions), but the numbers are made up. In production, you'd pull this from your claims data lake or EDW.
